<i>noun</i>: 통폐합 [통ː폐합/통ː페합], 통일 [통ː일], 일원화 [이뤈화], 단일화 [다닐화] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>통폐합 [통ː폐합/통ː페합]</dt><br>
<dd>merger; unification; closing</dd><br>
<dd>여러 개의 조직이나 기구 등을 없애거나 합쳐서 하나로 만듦.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making multiple organizations, groups, etc., into one, by closing down or combining all or part of them.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>통일 [통ː일]</dt><br>
<dd>1. unification</dd><br>
<dd>나누어지거나 갈라진 것들을 합쳐서 하나가 되게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of combining what has been divided or split into one.</dd><br>
<dd>2. standardization; equalization</dd><br>
<dd>서로 다른 것들을 같게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making different things the same.</dd><br>
<dd>3. concentration</dd><br>
<dd>여러 가지 생각을 버리고 정신이나 마음을 집중함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of pushing out many thoughts and making one’s mind or heart focus on something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일원화 [이뤈화]</dt><br>
<dd>unification</dd><br>
<dd>하나로 합함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of uniting things into one.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>단일화 [다닐화]</dt><br>
<dd>simplification; unification</dd><br>
<dd>여럿인 것이 하나로 됨. 또는 하나로 만듦.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which many different things become one, or the act of unifying many different things into one.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>